        "timestamp": "2018-03-26 18:22:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLusheng, as you asked, I uploaded a generic redis cluster.\nPlease add the script you mentioned that adds hosts to cluster.\nPlease add it under kubernetes/redis/resources/scripts directory and map it via configMap to the statefulset. After that you would need to add the postStart hook that would run it. Or it can be run using \"command\" in background and periodically check whether new pods were added, and add them to the cluster.\nHope this helps.",
        "patchset_number": 1
