        "message": "Patch Set 14:\n\n> I cannot reproduce this in my local testing (it is not a Helm based\n > system though so it is not exactly the same).  One previous\n > experience we had the same problem was due to quoting around the\n > list of nodes (IP:port), -- the command expects a list of\n > arguments, not single argument with space between. Since I do not\n > know how Helm does the processing here I do not know whether this\n > applies here.  So just adding a paste processing to see if this\n > fixes the problem.\n\nStill same.\nIn order to have helm you just need to download and install it:\nwget http://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-helm/helm-v2.7.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz\ntar -zxvf helm-v2.7.1-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nmv linux-amd64/helm /usr/local/bin/helm\n\nOutput of the script:\n+ sleep 10\n+ echo '====> Configure the cluster'\n====> Configure the cluster\n++ echo 10.244.4.102:6379 10.244.1.93:6379 10.244.3.101:6379 10.244.2.91:6379 10.244.5.82:6379 10.244.5.83:6379\n++ paste -s\n+ redis-trib create --replicas 1 10.244.4.102:6379 10.244.1.93:6379 10.244.3.101:6379 10.244.2.91:6379 10.244.5.82:6379 10.244.5.83:6379\n>>> Creating cluster\n[ERR] Node 10.244.4.102:6379 is not configured as a cluster node.",
